div.div: Ore dake Level Up na Ken: Season 2 - Arise from the Shadow
The second season of Solo Leveling. Mastering his new abilities in secret, Jin-U must battle humanity's toughest foes to save his mother. (Source: Crunchyroll News)

High-school beauty Umaru seems like the perfect teen wunderkind, but she's hiding a shocking double life. As soon as she gets home, she becomes a junk-food-inhaling, soda-guzzling, video-game-addicted slob. The only one who sees this unsavory side of Umaru is her beleaguered older brother Taihei, who does his best to keep up with his work while trying to get his little sister to behave like a decent member of society. As she makes new friends and gets into a number of wacky situations, Umaru will continue to fight for her right to stay up all night binging potato chips and anime. (Source: Anime News Network)
Episodes included in the manga's seventh and tenth volume.

After getting revenge on the Thulcaan Empire, Jack Valantier took his last breath. But just when he thinks it's all over, he finds himself transported back to when he was 14! From his negligent and wicked family to his loyal servant and caring sister, it's all just as he had remembered. But this time, Jack is armed to the teeth with decades of experience from his previous life! He's ready to give them hell, and those that have wronged him will pay dearly. Because this time, he's invincible.
(Source: Tapas)
Wo Zai Yijie De Shi Shen Zhi Lu

Chen Zhiliao is a modern straight-A student and a Kendo genius. He picked up gaming to woo a girl, but unexpectedly, he was struck by lightning and was transmitted into the game. Moreover, he could not log out! He tried to survive in the game, but he didn't expect to meet a powerful monster right at the beginning! Will the monster kill him, and game over? Or will he defeat the powerful monster?
(Source: WebComics)

Ehan was a stressed-out graduate student who vowed to never attend school again, until he was reborn as the third son of a noble family of mages. But since he isn't the sole heir, he has to make his own path by enrolling at Einrogard, the best magic school in the empire. And although everyone expects much from him, Ehan's time in academia has taught him that getting easy As is the best way to get through school. Despite his lack of ambition, can he graduate as a full-fledged mage?
(Source: Tapas)
Doukyonin ga Konoyo no Mon Janai
Comedy, Ecchi, Horror, Romance, Slice of Life, Supernatural

The young man's new apartment is haunted, but as it turns out, even the dead have their own personal shortcomings... issues of the flesh included.
For the dead have lingering desires and are more susceptible to the world of the living than what one may think. There's anger, there's hate, there's curiosity... and there's love too.
Here he finds a ghastly girl who observes him quietly, certainly desiring something...

My name is Yu Il-Sin, a third-rate web novel author. I discovered a strange gaming app and was judged to be a G-rank hunter. You save the world in the game and gain divine powers you can use in real life. It's a little bit strange, somehow? My follower count and the number of quests keep increasing. In the midst of this, when should I write my web novel? It's suspended for personal reasons... No, I'm starting the serialization. (Source: Naver, translated) Note: Chapter count includes a prologue.
